longBusinessSummary: As of January 14, 2017, Harvest Community Bank  was acquired by First-Citizens Bank & Trust Company. Harvest Community Bank provides various commercial banking products and services to small and medium-sized businesses, professionals, and individuals in New Jersey, the United States. It accepts various deposit products, including personal and business checking accounts, individual retirement accounts, business money market accounts, statement savings, and term certificate accounts, as well as multi-tiered personal savings accounts. The company also offers business and personal loans comprising commercial loans; commercial lines of credit; mortgage loans; commercial and residential construction loans; letters of credit; and consumer loans. In addition, it provides Internet banking, and safe deposit boxes, as well as ATMs at branch locations. The company operates four full service branch locations in Pennsville, Pilesgrove Township, Elmer, and Salem, New Jersey. Harvest Community Bank was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Pennsville, New Jersey.
